<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="a27Sep1925"><font color="red">27 September 1925</font> <i>Letters I</i> (to Harriet Weaver): I cannot make head or tail of Mr Walsh&apos;s review <i>This Quarter</i>. Miss Beach and I have written and wired &hellip; but cannot get any answer. Nobody knows where he or <i>Shem</i> is. He (Mr Walsh) proposed that Pound correct my proofs. I wrote to to Mr Pound assuring him that I wanted nothing better than to check them myself and asking him would it be possible to have my piece set first &hellip;  </div>
